  "summary": {
    "en": "Marketing literature views word-of-mouth (WOM) as unidirectional communication in which consumers transmit either positive or negative messages based on their consumption experiences. Becoming visible in online forums, however, are consumers who engage in WOM as part of interactions with other consumers. This article aims to investigate a phenomenon frequently occurring in these interactions: consumers who defend companies and brands against others’ negative WOM."
  },
  "title": {
    "en": "Trash talk rebuffed: consumers' defense of companies criticized in online communities"
